03/07/2006
BACKA TOPOLA, Serbia -- Serbian Parliament Speaker Predrag Markovic and Hungarian counterpart Katalin Szili expressed their satisfaction with the decline in the number of reported interethnic incidents in Vojvodina, during their meeting Sunday (2 July) in Backa Topola. 
They also voiced readiness to boost co-operation between the two countries' institutions on projects aimed at increasing interethnic tolerance and co-existence. 
Local authorities in Vojvodina say the number of ethnically motivated incidents in the region fell by 70 per cent in the first half of 2006, compared to the same period in 2005. 
(Tanjug, RTS - 02/07/06)
